@startuml workload-auth-modes
' How the gateway derives a trustworthy namespace: the mTLS path, the bearer path, and the shared cross-check.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/llm/workload-identity.md
!include _style.puml

start
:LLM proxy request arrives on **:8443**;

if (Client certificate presented?) then (**yes: Mode 1, mTLS**)

  :Verified against **kaalm-ca** at the handshake\n(a cert failing CA verification is rejected at the\nhandshake itself: no HTTP response, no error body);

  :Scan the DNS SAN **list** for a recognized suffix:\n**.svc.cluster.local** or **.task.kaalm.io**\n(short-form Service SANs match neither: ignored);

  if (Exactly **one** recognized SAN, with **exactly**\nthe expected label count of **5** for either shape) then (no)
    :**403 invalid_cert**;
    note left
      Defense in depth against a
      dotted-name bypass: if rule 21
      were relaxed, name "admin.svc"
      in namespace "team-a" gives a
      6-label SAN, rejected **before**
      the namespace extractor runs.
    end note
    stop
  else (yes)
  endif

  :**namespace = SAN label at index 1**\n(the second label; identical for both shapes,\nwhich differ only in workload type);

else (**no: Mode 2, bearer**)

  :**Step 0: Pod-ownership precheck**\n**Runs FIRST. Never cached.**\nResolve the source IP to a Pod (informer cache);
  note right #FFE4B5
    **The ordering is the**
    **security property.**
    It precedes TokenReview, so
    a hostile Pod cannot exploit
    TokenReview latency or outage.
    Uncached because Pod identity
    at a source IP changes, so a
    token-cache hit cannot skip it.
  end note

  if (Pod ownerRef -> **Agent** / **AgentTask**, or carries\nthe Kaalm-managed label set?) then (yes)
    :**401 unauthorized**\nregardless of the token presented;
    note right
      **This blocks the auth**
      **downgrade.** Kaalm-managed
      Pods MUST use mTLS, so a
      compromised Agent Pod cannot
      fall back to its SA token as
      a second credential.
    end note
    stop
  else (no)
  endif

  if (Token cache hit? (SHA-256 of the token)) then (no)
    :POST **TokenReview**, audience **kaalm-gateway**;

    if (apiserver reachable?) then (no)
      :**503 internal_unavailable**\nretryable: true, **Retry-After: 1**\n(mTLS and cached-token callers unaffected);
      stop
    else (yes)
    endif

    if (status.authenticated?) then (no)
      :**401 unauthorized**;
      stop
    else (yes)
    endif

    :**namespace = middle segment of**\n**status.user.username**\nsystem:serviceaccount:**<namespace>**:<sa>;
    :**Cache the result.** TTL from the token's own\n**exp** claim, minus a 60s margin, capped at\n5 min (not a JWT: fixed 5 min);
  else (yes)
    :namespace from cache;
  endif
endif

:**Source-IP-to-Pod cross-check (both modes)**\nThe Pod at the source IP must be in the\nnamespace authentication just established;
note right
  Runs **after** authentication,
  never instead of it. Crypto and
  topological attestation must
  agree, catching a stolen cert or
  token replayed from another Pod.
end note

if (namespace matches?) then (no)
  :**401 unauthorized**;
  stop
else (yes)
endif

:Proceed to provider routing;
stop

legend bottom
  **Neither** a client cert nor an Authorization header: **401**.
  **Both**: the mTLS path wins and the bearer token is ignored.
endlegend
@enduml
